The BTB (broad-complex, tram track, and bric-abrac) proteins are involved in 
developmental processes, biotic, and abiotic stress responses in various plants, 
but the molecular basis of protein interactions is yet to be investiagted in 
rice. In this study, the identified BTB proteins were divided into BTB-TAZ, 
MATH-BTB, BTB-NPH, BTB-ANK, BTB-Skp, BTB-DUF, and BTB-TPR subfamilies based on 
